<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>pyvideo.org: Videos of Martin Pretorius</title><link>http://www.pyvideo.org/speaker/2000/martin-pretorius/rss</link><description></description><atom:link href="http://www.pyvideo.org/speaker/2000/martin-pretorius/rss" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 03 Oct 2014 00:00:00 -0500</lastBuildDate><ttl>500</ttl><item><title>Inspired by Lisp to get Ruby to talk Python</title><link>http://www.pyvideo.org/video/3829/inspired-by-lisp-to-get-ruby-to-talk-python</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Abstract&lt;/p&gt;
Having pushed Ruby to the limits of what it can accomplish in terms of number crunching and data analysis, we looked around for another solution in the data analysis and modelling space. We quickly found that with packages and tools like Numpy, Pandas, the iPython Notebook and new packages like Blaze, Python looked to be a good language fit.
Porting a large existing codebase and accompanying infrastructure from a Ruby to Python ecosystem simply wasn't an option, so we had to do something clever (and fun!).
This talk will be about how we managed to leverage the power of Python while retaining our modelling code in Ruby (and opening up opportunity for other languages), by embracing Lispâ€™s code-is-data philosophy.</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Martin Pretorius</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 03 Oct 2014 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://www.pyvideo.org/video/3829/inspired-by-lisp-to-get-ruby-to-talk-python</guid><enclosure url="http://archive.org/download/pyconza2014-inspired-by-lisp/9%20B%20Inspired%20by%20Lisp%20to%20get%20Ruby%20to%20talk%20Python-.ogv" length="None" type="video/ogg"></enclosure><media:group><media:content url="http://archive.org/download/pyconza2014-inspired-by-lisp/9%20B%20Inspired%20by%20Lisp%20to%20get%20Ruby%20to%20talk%20Python-.ogv" mime_type="video/ogg"></media:content><media:content url="http://archive.org/download/pyconza2014-inspired-by-lisp/9%20B%20Inspired%20by%20Lisp%20to%20get%20Ruby%20to%20talk%20Python-.mp4" mime_type="video/mp4"></media:content></media:group><media:thumbnail url="http://archive.org/download/pyconza2014-inspired-by-lisp/pyconza2014-inspired-by-lisp.thumbs/9%20B%20Inspired%20by%20Lisp%20to%20get%20Ruby%20to%20talk%20Python-_000090.jpg"></media:thumbnail></item></channel></rss>